*******************************IN SHORT IMP *****
==============================
1. OOP CORE (MUST KNOW)
==============================

Encapsulation — hide internal state, expose behavior via methods
Abstraction — show what, hide how
Inheritance — is-a relationship (prefer composition over inheritance)
Polymorphism — same interface, different implementations

Key rule:
→ Prefer composition over deep inheritance


==============================
2. SOLID (ONLY WHAT MATTERS)
==============================

SRP — one class = one responsibility
OCP — extend, don’t modify existing code
DIP — depend on interfaces, not concrete classes


==============================
3. MUST-DO DESIGN PATTERNS (CORE 7)
==============================

CREATIONAL
- Singleton (thread-safe)
- Factory Method
- Builder

STRUCTURAL
- Adapter
- Decorator
- Facade

BEHAVIORAL (MOST IMPORTANT)
- Strategy
- Observer
- State


==============================
4. PATTERN IDENTIFICATION (VERY IMPORTANT)
==============================

Strategy → swap algorithm (payment, sorting)
State → behavior changes with status (order, vending machine)
Observer → notify many (notifications, events)
Decorator → add features dynamically (toppings, addons)
Factory → choose object type (payment, notifications)
Builder → step-by-step object creation
Singleton → only one instance (logger, config)


==============================
5. MUST-DO LLD PROBLEMS
==============================

- Parking Lot System
- LRU Cache
- Elevator System
- Splitwise
- Vending Machine
